Inline HTML elements

HTML defines a long list of available inline tags, a complete list of which can be found on the Mozilla Developer Network.

  • To bold text, use **To bold text**.
  • To italicize text, use *To italicize text*.
  • Abbreviations, like HTML should be defined like this *[HTML]: HyperText Markup Language.
  • Citations, like — Mark otto, should use <cite>.
  • Deleted text should use ~~deleted~~ and inserted text should use <ins>.
  • Superscript text uses <sup> and subscript text uses <sub>.

Most of these elements are styled by browsers with few modifications on our part.

About

I am a Games Development student who has recently finished their Third Year in IT Sligo. I have a keen interest in video games as a medium and would consider myself an aficionado of video game soundtracks (OSTs).

Highly proficient in spelling and grammar from an early age, I am now focused on improving my programming and problem-solving skills both through coursework and during my free time. Known to take work seriously, I like to ensure it is done well and on-time. Currently, I am well-versed in C# programming with GameMaker, XNA and Unity.
